results.name: Least number k that can be written as k^2 * j with 0 < j <= k and gcd(k, j) = 1 in n ways.
mathematica: t = Sort[ Flatten[ Table[n = k^2*j; If[ GCD[k, j] == 1 && 10^5 < n < 10^8, n, {}], {k, 15000}, {j, k}]]]; l = Length[t]; t[[Select[ Range[l - 11], t[[ # ]] == t[[ # + 9]] &]]]
results.author: _Leroy Quet_ and _Robert G. Wilson v_, Feb 23 2005
